headline: These 5 Artificial Intelligence (AI) Stocks Make Up 28.8% of the Entire S&P 500 Index
summary: The S&P 500 (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC) is home to 500 companies from 11 different sectors of the economy, making it the most diversified of the major U.S. stock market indexes.  The S&P 500 delivered a return of 25% during 2024, whereas the S&P 500 Equal Weight index, which assigns the same weighting to every stock regardless of its market cap, was up by just 10%.

headline: Apple Stock Was Hot, Hot, Hot in 2024. Now It Faces a Tougher Test.
summary: Apple stock has backed off its all-time high to close the year worth over $3.8 trillion, and within striking distance of being the first company ever to hit $4 trillion.

headline: Europe stunned the world with its ‘regulatory tsunami’ this year—but AI and Trump will add new snags in 2025
summary: The EU went after Big Tech in 2024 unlike before. The new year will add more players to the regulatory tussle, including Donald Trump and Elon Musk.
